commitResults.messageBody:
run() and main() method in Duke are not used.

run() and main() method are not needed for the current Gui-based Duke
when we transitioned from text-based Duke.

Let's delete the run() and main() method in Duke.

Deleting dead code makes the code base cleaner and easier to maintain.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor TaskList, Ui and Task class
Change Parser to include a default statement for switch statement
Extract method of saving file in saveFile method of Storage class
commitResults.messageBody:
saveFile method has a method implementation to write to file.

The method implementation may have violate SLAP..

Let's extract out the method implementation and place it in a separate
method called writeToFile.

This will make it easier to read and debug in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Javadoc for greetUser and showError method
Remove try-catch block in Parser
commitResults.messageBody:
IdentifyCommand method in Parser has a try-catch block for cases when a user
does not specify additional required arguments.

There is an inconsistency in some Commands returning their own custom
message if user does not enter additional arguments before a switch
statement was used.

Let's standardize it across the commands for all of them to return
custom messages if user is short of arguments required for command.

It is easier to find out what user argument is lacking from a specified
message rather than a catch-all message.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update ParserTest test cases
Add sort functionality to task list
commitResults.messageBody:
Task list currently displays tasks as they were added in.

A sorted chronological list may help users see which tasks are upcoming.

Let's,
* add a sort functionality to TaskList
* add a test case in TaskListText

sortTask uses Comparator to sort the Tasks and places earlier task at the top
since users are more likely to look at earlier tasks. todo task is assumed to have
less urgency since they do not have a date attached to it.
